# Home fingerprint avatar carousel

## Product rule

The carousel must show **every** PNG data URI the backend returns in `avatar_urls` (newest first), or the single `avatar_url` when history is absent.

## Do not

- **Do not cap** visible slides using counts from `/api/analytics/my-events`, PostHog, or other merged event samples. Those responses are **sparse** (limits, deduplication, partial warehouse coverage) and routinely imply **fewer distinct UTC days** than the number of stored `avatar_pngs`, which **hides real portraits** and breaks UX.

## Do

- Normalize payloads with `portraitDataUrisFromAvatarPayload` in `lib/home-fingerprint-avatar-portraits.ts` (single source of truth).
- Add or extend **unit tests** in `lib/home-fingerprint-avatar-portraits.test.ts` when changing parsing.
- Keep **Playwright** coverage in `e2e/avatar-generation.spec.ts` that asserts multiple `avatar_urls` remain visible when `my-events` returns a single-day sample.

## Server bound

The authoritative upper bound on history length is **`MAX_AVATAR_PNG_HISTORY`** (Rust) and what Cosmos/Scylla stores — not client-side analytics heuristics.
